{
  "specVersion": "0.4.0",
  "kind": "tsm-scene",
  "id": "store-household",
  "title": "Store and household linked by a transaction",
  "source": "Adapted from Baldwin (2026), <em>A theory of technology and organizations</em>, Figure 4",
  "lenses": ["coordinator-dispatch", "modularity-boundary"],

  "narrative": {
    "mode": "walkthrough",
    "steps": [
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 1.</strong> A single TSM holds two transaction-free zones — a Store (S1–S5) and a Household (H1–H5) — with a coordinator (CG) at the top. Each zone runs its own internal recipe; the diagonal lays them out side by side.",
        "reveal": { "include": ["diagonal"] }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 2.</strong> The coordinator dispatches downward. CG seeds every task in both zones; <em>inside</em> each zone, tasks transfer freely to one another the way a job shop does. No formal accounting required — these are transfers, not transactions.",
        "reveal": { "include": ["diagonal", "transfer:directed:forward"] },
        "setEmphasis": {
          "primary": { "byLens": ["coordinator-dispatch"] }
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 3.</strong> The off-diagonal regions between Store and Household are mostly empty. <em>That</em> is the transaction-free-zone insight: firms are dense inside and sparse at the boundary. Two single marks bridge the zones — one knife transfer below the diagonal (S5 → H1) and one money transfer above it (H1 → S5).",
        "reveal": { "include": ["diagonal", "transfer:directed:forward", "transfer:directed:backward"] },
        "setEmphasis": {
          "primary": { "byId": ["S5→H1", "H1→S5"] },
          "secondary": { "byLens": ["coordinator-dispatch"] }
        }
      },
      {
        "caption": "<strong>Step 4.</strong> The cluster borders make the two transaction-free zones visible. The thin crossing point between them is where the transaction lives — defining what's exchanged, counting the items, compensating for them. Modularization is what created the thinness; the transaction is what the thinness now affords.",
        "reveal": {
          "include": [
            "diagonal",
            "transfer:directed:forward",
            "transfer:directed:backward",
            "overlay:module-border",
            "highlight:cross-region"
          ]
        },
        "setEmphasis": {
          "primary": { "byLens": ["modularity-boundary"] }
        }
      }
    ]
  },

